'''Kolpik''' is a type of traditional headgear worn in families of many [[Chassidic]] [[Rebbes]] (Hasidic rabbis), by unmarried children on [[Shabbat]] and by Rebbes on special occasions.
[[image:Belz1.jpg|thumb|The third Belzer Rebbe, Yissachar Dov Rokeach (I) wearing a "kolpik"]]
it is a made from brown fur, as opposed to a [[spodik]], worn by polish [[chassidic]] dynasties, which is fashioned out of black fur.
